
<div class="alert alert-danger">
	<p>Child</p>
	<p>@Str</p>

	<br>
	<p>@MSG</p>

</div>



@code {
	[Parameter]
	public string Str { get; set; } = "Hello From Child";

	[Parameter]
	public string MSG { get; set; } = "Default";
}


@*
📘 Case 1: Parent → Direct Child Component

In this case, the parent component (`/p1`) passes a string parameter to the child component.

✅ Steps to pass a parameter:

1️⃣ In the Parent:
    <ChildComponent Str="Message from parent" />

2️⃣ In the Child:
    Use [Parameter] to receive the value:
        [Parameter]
        public string Str { get; set; } = "Hello From Child";

🧠 Notes:
- The `Str` property in the child will receive the value `"Message from parent"` when rendered.
- This is the most straightforward way to pass data down the component tree.

*@

